http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/karnataka/Free-yoga-camp-in-Hubballi/article13989408.ece

A mega eight-day yoga camp will be held in Hubballi from January 17 with an objective to sensitise the general public on the advantages of yoga and adapting a healthy lifestyle. Yoga guru Sri Vachananand Swami will conduct the camp and also provide naturopathy treatment to participants. Entry is free.President of the Yoga and Satsang Samiti Shankranna Munavalli, convenor and former MLC Mohan Limbikai told presspersons here on Tuesday that the objective of the camp, Yoga Vijnana Shibira, was to spread the message of “Yoga as facilitator for healthy India”.Mr. Limbikai said that a four-acre land on the premises of K.S. Sharma Institute on Gokul Road here was being spruced up for the mega camp that would go on till January 24, daily at 6 a.m. to 7.30 a.m.He said that during the yoga camp, satsang would be held in the evening from 6 p.m. to 8 p.m. and various religious heads, including Sri Shivaratri Deshikendra Swami of Suttur Mutt and Sri Siddheshwar Swami of Vijayapura, would deliver discourses.For more details call M. Eshwar on Ph: 9448822245 9480733568.